&lt;p&gt;The Medical Secretary provides essential administrative and clerical support to ensure efficient operations at Rhode Island Primary Care&amp;nbsp;Medical Group. This position serves as a critical communication hub between patients, providers, clinical staff, and external stakeholders in a multi-site medical practice environment. The Medical Secretary maintains accurate medical records, manages scheduling and correspondence, and ensures seamless coordination of patient care activities.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you’ll do &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Front Office Operations:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Greet patients and visitors in a professional and welcoming manner&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Check in patients, verify demographics and insurance information in Epic EHR&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collect co-payments and process patient payments using point-of-sale systems&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Schedule, reschedule, and confirm patient appointments across multiple providers and locations&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage provider calendars and optimize appointment scheduling&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Respond to patient inquiries via phone, email, and patient portal messages&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Register new patients and update existing patient information&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Medical Records and Documentation:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain accurate and confidential patient medical records in Epic EHR&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Scan, file, and organize medical documents and correspondence&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
